annotation.TEXT: Luckily, power ups themselves aren't restricted. I just can't hit a block to obtain them!
Ow. Good thing I got those mushrooms earlier!
Nuts! Well, not much I can do about that...
And now, we wait... (I probably should've sped this part up, but whatever.)
Now, hitting enemies is outlawed, but I don't think having them transform into coins from the goal is the same thing!
Find out next time! ...Just kidding!
It actually is possible to make that jump. I just needed a speed boost from a slope earlier in the level! (Good luck trying to do this tool-less, though!)
Uh, oh! Quick! Let me out of here before buzzy gets me!
Yes! Now, just dodge these spike tops, then avoid the goal tape to finish this!
And, as a bonus, I can make it to the secret exit's room with time to spare!
Back to Donut Plains 2! Also, I'm back to non-TAS mode now.
Now, the greatest threats in this level are the Hammer Bros. and the Cheep-Cheeps.
Alright, it's finally time for Awesome!
There might be a use for the P-switch later, but it would be incredibly difficult to carry without running, so I'm not going to bother.
The baseball Chucks are a pain. I have to move skillfully to avoid them completely.
Oh, god... The cheepos... But I do get a free flower here, which gives me an extra hit if I need it.
Also, fortunately, my coins happened to be prime once again!

Without being able to get at least nine coins, I'm forced to enter the slope and parakoopa filled second area, and since that area lacks a Yoshi coin, I can't collect more than three Yoshi coins in this level. Nuts!
Find out next time!
But... Is it really impossible?
But, what will my next challenge be like?
Yoshi coin! Me want!
Now, I need to reach the normal exit.
Uh... What's with the music? I don't know... Just pretend the water's black and it'll fit right in.
My bonus stars seem to love prime numbers too, but that isn't required.
BGM: Castlevania - Lost Life
No running. No Yoshi. No hitting blocks or enemies. If I get a cape, use spin jumps only. Collect every Yoshi coin that I can. And, finish each level with my coins showing a prime number over 10.
Haw, haw!
Now, with the tide up, if I go down here and duck, the current will push me into the Yoshi coin with no problems!
It's necessary to get a speed boost from a slope to make at least one of the larger jumps here.
Watch out for Rexes that could suddenly change direction on you due to a cheepo!
Same deal as before for the first two rooms, except I don't have to beat a strict time limit this time.
That Yoshi coin looks tricky...
Awesome's done, but since I'm super now, there's one little bit of unfinished business I need to take care of...
BGM: Mega Man 7 - Freeze Man's Stage
Ooh, found a safe spot by ducking right here! Nice!
Oh, this ought to be good.
SMW challenge from gariel4: Clear Awesome, Mondo, Donut Plains 2, and Chocolate Island 2 (both exits) under the following conditions:
I decided to start with Donut Plains 2 (obviously). I'll save the tougher levels for later.
Oops... A koopa keeled over off screen for some reason. I didn't hit him myself, though!
Now, my coins are already at an appropriate prime number, so just make sure to hit the goal tape.
What the? There's a spot in the side of this yellow chunk that my fireballs go through! That's weird!
BGM: Zelda: Oracle of Seasons - Tarm Ruins
Fortunately, I did have enough speed, along with a prime number of coins once again! Now, let's get 50 stars from the ground without running!
I didn't hit those guys! It was that koopa up there that did it!
Yes, barely. Now, I figured this part out ahead of time, and for my coins to land on a prime number from here, just get everybody on screen and don't hit the tape.
This part can get tricky. Stay towards the left side, or else you might be stuck under a ceiling that's too low to let you jump over a buzzy.
Argh! I hit the Banzai... But, it doesn't matter anyway. The next jump is five tiles high, and without running or stomping something, I can't make it! It's impossible I tell you!
Okay! And, once again, my coins landed perfectly on a prime number for me!
And, with only three Yoshi coins, I must enter this particular final area. Can I make this jump?
BGM: Dead or Alive - Right Around
Okay, let's try that again, shall we?
Next stop, Chocolate Island 2. This one ended up taking me several tries.
With running restricted, slopes can give a nice speed boost if used properly.
Watch out! Mustn't crush! Mustn't kill!
Whew... That was close.
One tosses projectiles everywhere that can knock me silly, and the other can cause me to instantly fail just by flopping into me! Suddenly, the move Splash sounds very dangerous!
Yes! Now, to get the key to the keyhole without running, I'll can press Y while I'm standing still and inch it over, little by little.
But, is it possible to reach the secret exit without running? Is it possible to even make all the necessary jumps in this area without running?
This was one of my more embarrassing failures, and I thought it was funny enough to leave in!
Whoa! Evil fish! Get away!
Find out next time! ...Just kidding again!
Unfortunately, with the current restrictions, I can only get four coins in the first room. What does that mean?
Uh, dude? The timer's below 250 now, so why aren't you entering?
Since I'm going for Yoshi coins, I'm not taking the secret exit route.
Done this way, I get exactly 23 coins added to my account, which just so happens to land me on another prime number! I sure have been getting lucky with that!
Fortunately, these steps aren't a problem!
In addition to clearing the five tile high jump, I need enough speed for the huge jump at the end!
This jump is just barely makeable, but then after that, I'll have slope power backing me up!
The bonus stars end up becoming square here, but that's fine. Square numbers are awesome!
Guess what? It's TAS time!
I'll just speed up most of this, since it's mostly the same.
This jump is tough, but not impossible.
Now all that's left is Awesome and Mondo. I'm going to save Awesome for last.
BGM: Sonic 2 - Oil Ocean Zone
Uh... Can I even reach that Yoshi coin?
BGM: Pokmon GSC - Dark Cave
However, I also need every coin here, too. Otherwise, I won't be able to reach a prime number greater than 10!
Well, to make things a bit easier, I want to enter the mushroom filled third area, and for that I need to wait until the timer is below 235.
Now, in case you hadn't guessed, I'm back to get this Yoshi coin I missed before. Now that I'm super, I can just barely reach it.
Challenge complete! (It's too bad there's no way to get more Yoshi coins in CI2 without breaking another rule.)
I'll just make use of this safe spot again while I wait for the tide. (I might not have even had to duck here.)
